    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-26T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="756"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Stettinius Mission/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-26T22:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 26, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 26—9:27 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3443. Deles No. 34. From the Under Secretary. During their talks on Saudi Arabia
                    Sir Maurice Peterson and Murray agreed as to the desirability of accelerating
                    consideration of the Saudi Arabian financial <pb facs="0704" n="692"
                        xml:id="pg_692"/> problem, and particularly of the proposals for the
                    establishment of a currency system, now under discussion between the Department
                    and the Treasury and the British Embassy.<note n="83" xml:id="d756fn83">See
                        footnote 47, <ref target="#pg_674">p. 674</ref>.</note> Since this is
                    closely related to the question of a goods subsidy program and the contemplated
                    shipment of further supplies of silver from the United States, which the British
                    consider undesirable, I hope the Department can expedite action on this subject
                    in Washington. [Stettinius.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
